\begin_layout Standard
Norway Spruce (
\begin_inset Flex Emph
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Picea abies
\end_layout

\end_inset

) is a commercially significant conifer with a ubiquitous distribution throughou
t most of Finland.
 Norway Spruce accounts for 34% of total forest products in Finland, which
 includes timber and other wood based forest products 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Scand.2003a"

\end_inset

.
 Because of it's significant impact on the Finnish economy, it is important
 to understand and to address issues which negativly affect the growth and
 production of Norway Spruce.
 The most devastating pathogen affecting the growth of Norway Spruce is
 butt rot caused by the 
\begin_inset Flex Emph
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Heterobasidion annosum
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\emph on
sl
\emph default
 species complex.
 Damages to forest production in Europe from 
\emph on
Heterobasidion spp
\emph default
.
 is greater than 800 million euros annually 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Asiegbu2005"

\end_inset

; as such, it is important to study the pathogen and host to better understand
 the complex nature of infection biology and resistance factors which hold
 the potential for mitigating losses and improving forest yeilds in areas
 where 
\emph on
Heterobasidion spp.

\emph default
 are prevalent.
 
